   994  	UID(ctx context.Context, obj *v1alpha1.StressChaos) (string, error)
   995  
   996  	CreationTimestamp(ctx context.Context, obj *v1alpha1.StressChaos) (*time.Time, error)
   997  	DeletionTimestamp(ctx context.Context, obj *v1alpha1.StressChaos) (*time.Time, error)
   998  
   999  	Labels(ctx context.Context, obj *v1alpha1.StressChaos) (map[string]interface{}, error)
  1000  	Annotations(ctx context.Context, obj *v1alpha1.StressChaos) (map[string]interface{}, error)
  1001  
  1002  	Podstress(ctx context.Context, obj *v1alpha1.StressChaos) ([]*model.PodStressChaos, error)
  1003  }
  1004  type StressChaosSpecResolver interface {
  1005  	Mode(ctx context.Context, obj *v1alpha1.StressChaosSpec) (string, error)
  1006  }
  1007  type StressChaosStatusResolver interface {

  1009  }

  4174  func (e *executableSchema) Exec(ctx context.Context) graphql.ResponseHandler {
  4175  	rc := graphql.GetOperationContext(ctx)
  4176  	ec := executionContext{rc, e}
  4177  	first := true
  4178  
  4179  	switch rc.Operation.Operation {
  4180  	case ast.Query:
  4181  		return func(ctx context.Context) *graphql.Response {
  4182  			if !first {
  4183  				return nil
  4184  			}
  4185  			first = false
  4186  			data := ec._Query(ctx, rc.Operation.SelectionSet)
  4187  			var buf bytes.Buffer
  4188  			data.MarshalGQL(&buf)
  4189  
  4190  			return &graphql.Response{
  4191  				Data: buf.Bytes(),
  4192  			}
  4193  		}
  4194  	case ast.Mutation:
  4195  		return func(ctx context.Context) *graphql.Response {
  4196  			if !first {
  4197  				return nil
  4198  			}
  4199  			first = false
  4200  			data := ec._Mutation(ctx, rc.Operation.SelectionSet)
  4201  			var buf bytes.Buffer
  4202  			data.MarshalGQL(&buf)
  4203  
  4204  			return &graphql.Response{
  4205  				Data: buf.Bytes(),
  4206  			}
  4207  		}
  4208  	case ast.Subscription:
  4209  		next := ec._Logger(ctx, rc.Operation.SelectionSet)
  4210  
  4211  		var buf bytes.Buffer
  4212  		return func(ctx context.Context) *graphql.Response {
  4213  			buf.Reset()
  4214  			data := next()
  4215  
  4216  			if data == nil {
  4217  				return nil
  4218  			}
  4219  			data.MarshalGQL(&buf)
  4220  
  4221  			return &graphql.Response{
  4222  				Data: buf.Bytes(),
  4223  			}
  4224  		}
  4225  
  4226  	default:
  4227  		return graphql.OneShot(graphql.ErrorResponse(ctx, "unsupported GraphQL operation"))
  4228  	}
  4229  }
  4230  
  4231  type executionContext struct {

  4233  	*executableSchema
  4234  }

  4237  	if ec.DisableIntrospection {

  4240  	return introspection.WrapSchema(parsedSchema), nil
  4241  }

  4246  	}
  4247  	return introspection.WrapTypeFromDef(parsedSchema, parsedSchema.Types[name]), nil

  4419  # PodStatus represents information about the status of a pod. Status may trail the actual
  4420  # state of a system, especially if the node that hosts the pod cannot contact the control
  4421  # plane.
  4422  type PodStatus @goModel(model: "k8s.io/api/core/v1.PodStatus") {
  4423      # The phase of a Pod is a simple, high-level summary of where the Pod is in its lifecycle.
  4424      # The conditions array, the reason and message fields, and the individual container status
  4425      # arrays contain more detail about the pod's status.
  4426      # There are five possible phase values:
  4427      #
  4428      # Pending: The pod has been accepted by the Kubernetes system, but one or more of the
  4429      # container images has not been created. This includes time before being scheduled as
  4430      # well as time spent downloading images over the network, which could take a while.
  4431      # Running: The pod has been bound to a node, and all of the containers have been created.
  4432      # At least one container is still running, or is in the process of starting or restarting.
  4433      # Succeeded: All containers in the pod have terminated in success, and will not be restarted.
  4434      # Failed: All containers in the pod have terminated, and at least one container has
  4435      # terminated in failure. The container either exited with non-zero status or was terminated
  4436      # by the system.
  4437      # Unknown: For some reason the state of the pod could not be obtained, typically due to an
  4438      # error in communicating with the host of the pod.
  4439      #
  4440      # More info: https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/pods/pod-lifecycle#pod-phase
  4441      phase: String!
  4442  
  4443      # Current service state of pod.
  4444      # More info: https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/pods/pod-lifecycle#pod-conditions
  4445      conditions: [PodCondition!]
  4446  
  4447      # A human readable message indicating details about why the pod is in this condition.
  4448      message: String!
  4449  
  4450      # A brief CamelCase message indicating details about why the pod is in this state.
  4451      # e.g. 'Evicted'
  4452      reason: String!
  4453  
  4454      # nominatedNodeName is set only when this pod preempts other pods on the node, but it cannot be
  4455      # scheduled right away as preemption victims receive their graceful termination periods.
  4456      # This field does not guarantee that the pod will be scheduled on this node. Scheduler may decide
  4457      # to place the pod elsewhere if other nodes become available sooner. Scheduler may also decide to
  4458      # give the resources on this node to a higher priority pod that is created after preemption.
  4459      # As a result, this field may be different than PodSpec.nodeName when the pod is
  4460      # scheduled.
  4461      nominatedNodeName: String!
  4462  
  4463      # IP address of the host to which the pod is assigned. Empty if not yet scheduled.
  4464      hostIP: String!
  4465  
  4466      # IP address allocated to the pod. Routable at least within the cluster.
  4467      # Empty if not yet allocated.
  4468      podIP: String!
  4469  
  4470      # podIPs holds the IP addresses allocated to the pod. If this field is specified, the 0th entry must

  4472      # is empty if no IPs have been allocated yet.
  4473      podIPs: [PodIP!]
  4474  
  4475      # RFC 3339 date and time at which the object was acknowledged by the Kubelet.
  4476      # This is before the Kubelet pulled the container image(s) for the pod.
  4477      startTime: Time
  4478

  4480      # init container will have ready = true, the most recently started container will have
  4481      # startTime set.
  4482      # More info: https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/pods/pod-lifecycle#pod-and-container-status
  4483      initContainerStatuses: [ContainerStatus!]
  4484

  4487      # More info: https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/pods/pod-lifecycle#pod-and-container-status
  4488      containerStatuses: [ContainerStatus!]

  4493      qosClass: String!
